class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h𝓕</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Bounds/Defs.html#IsGLB\">IsGLB</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ <span class=\"fn\">𝓕'</span> ⊆ <span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕'</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Countable.html#Set.Countable\">Countable</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Bounds/Defs.html#IsGLB\">IsGLB</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝓕'</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If a function `s : X → E` can be written as the infimum of a family `𝓕` of upper semicontinuous\nfunctions then, assuming that `X` is hereditarily Lindelöf (for example, second countable),\n`s` can in fact be written as the infimum of some *countable* subfamily `𝓕'`.\n\nThis is implication a) ⇒ b) in\n[N. Bourbaki, *Topologie Générale*, Chapitre IX, Appendice I, Proposition 3][bourbaki1974]\n\nSee the module docstring for a discussion of the assumptions on `E`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Semicontinuity/Lindelof.html#exists_countable_upperSemicontinuous_isGLB","kind":"theorem","line":51,"name":"exists_countable_upperSemicontinuous_isGLB","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Topology/Semicontinuity/Lindelof.lean#L51-L85"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Topology.Semicontinuity.Basic","Mathlib.Topology.Compactness.Lindelof"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Topology.Semicontinuity.Lindelof"}